                        <Label prefHeight="124.0" prefWidth="860.0" text="Several key concepts form the foundation of effective management. Project Management Frameworks, such as PMBOK (Project Management Body of Knowledge), Agile, and Scrum, provide structured approaches to managing projects. Risk Management involves identifying, assessing, and mitigating risks that could impact the project. Efficient Resource Allocation ensures that time, money, and personnel are distributed effectively to maximize productivity and achieve project goals." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrapText="true">
