                        <Label prefHeight="91.0" prefWidth="848.0" text="The management process includes five main stages. During Initiation, the project is defined and necessary approvals are obtained. The Planning stage involves developing detailed project plans, including scope, schedule, and budget. Execution is the stage where people and resources are coordinated to carry out the project plan. Monitoring and Controlling involve tracking progress and making necessary adjustments. Finally, the Closing stage finalizes all project activities and formally closes the project." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrapText="true">
